fields.day1_exercises:
Warm-up: 10-15 minutes of brisk walking or light jogging

Flat Barbell Bench Press: 4 sets, 6-8 reps
Incline Dumbbell Press: 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Chest Dips (Weighted if possible): 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Chest Fly (Cable or Machine): 3 sets, 10-12 reps
Tricep Pushdown (Cable): 3 sets, 10-12 reps
Overhead Tricep Extension (Dumbbell): 3 sets, 10-12 reps

Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of chest and tricep stretches
fields.day2_exercises:
Warm-up: 10-15 minutes of light jogging or bike

Pull-ups (Weighted if possible): 4 sets, 6-8 reps
Barbell Deadlift: 4 sets, 6-8 reps
Seated Cable Row: 3 sets, 8-10 reps
One-Arm Dumbbell Row: 3 sets, 8-10 reps per side
Barbell Curl: 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Hammer Curl (Dumbbell): 3 sets, 10-12 reps

Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of back and bicep stretches
fields.day3_exercises:
Warm-up: 10-15 minutes on a stationary bike or brisk walking

Squat (Barbell): 4 sets, 6-8 reps
Leg Press: 4 sets, 8-10 reps
Romanian Deadlift (Dumbbells): 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Overhead Shoulder Press (Barbell or Dumbbells): 4 sets, 6-8 reps
Lateral Raise (Dumbbells): 3 sets, 10-12 reps
Front Raise (Dumbbells): 3 sets, 10-12 reps

Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of leg and shoulder stretches
fields.notes:
Aim for progressive overload by gradually increasing the weight or reps every week.
Focus on maintaining proper form for every exercise to prevent injury and maximize results.
Rest between sets should be 60-90 seconds for most exercises, but for compound lifts (like squats and deadlifts), you can take 90-120 seconds.
Make sure to stay hydrated and get enough protein for optimal muscle growth.
These programs are designed to balance both strength and hypertrophy (muscle growth) training.
